The Minister of Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs, Dr Nkosazana Dlamini Zuma leads the briefing. JOHANNESBURG - The restrictions on the sale of liquor will be lifted from Tuesday under level two regulations. The sale of liquor by licensed premises is permitted from 9am to 5pm, from Mondays to Thursdays. However, the sale of liquor is prohibited on Fridays, Saturdays, Sundays and public holidays. READ: Level 2 lockdown: Tavern owners keen to reopen These established have been permitted to operate with only a maximum of 50 patrons and observing health and hygiene protocols including washing of hands, sanitizing, wearing of masks and also a distance of 1.5 meters between patrons. Nightclubs will, however, remain closed during this period. The curfew between 10pm and 4am remains in place. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.